I"b<ol>
  <li>Into a bowl mix the flour with the salt.</li>
  <li>Melt the butter and add it to the bowl.</li>
  <li>Whisk the flour with the butter until the flour absorbs all of the butter.</li>
  <li>Add the yogurt and whisk the mix until it becomes a soft dough.</li>
  <li>Put the dough into the refrigerator for at least 1 hour before usage.</li>
  <li>Chop the apples into small pieces, pure them into a pot and boil until softened.</li>
  <li>Afterwards, remove all the water from the pot and smash the apples.</li>
  <li>Pure them into a strainer inorder to remove any excess water.</li>
  <li>Add them into a bowl and mix with the stevia and the cinnamon powder.</li>
  <li>Let it cool down before usage.</li>
  <li>Pre heat oven to 180°C.</li>
  <li>Remove the dough from the refrigerator. On a clean surface, pure some flour and roll the dough. Place the dough in an ovenproof dish. Remove any excess dough and create thin lanes.</li>
  <li>Pure the apples into the the dough and place the thin lanes from above to create a grid.</li>
  <li>Place the dish into the oven and bake it for 40’ - 45’.</li>
</ol>
